<p>Tuesday 1st May 1917<br/>Bapaume</p>
<p>Watered mules then gave them a run on the grabs till 11.30 am<br/>Cleaning up the mule lines in the afternoon.<br/>Paid 40 francs on e shilling and four pence left.<br/>Line Piquet at 5.15pm while taking of nose bags one of the mules took a liking to me and let fly his two hind legs. I got them all right so the Piquet had to get another man.</p>
